title: The BEST Easy Healthy Lasagna

extendedIngredients.name: zucchini
extendedIngredients.original: 2 cups finely diced zucchini (about 2 small or 1 medium/large zucchini)
extendedIngredients.originalName: finely diced zucchini (about 2 small or 1 medium/large zucchini)

extendedIngredients.name: summer squash
extendedIngredients.original: 1 cup finely diced summer squash (about 1 medium /large summer squash)
extendedIngredients.originalName: finely diced summer squash (about 1 medium /large summer squash)

extendedIngredients.name: canned tomatoes
extendedIngredients.original: 1 15 ounce can whole tomatoes (2 cups, or crushed tomatoes if preferred)
extendedIngredients.originalName: whole tomatoes (2 cups, or crushed tomatoes if preferred)

extendedIngredients.name: oven-ready lasagna noodles
extendedIngredients.original: 6 ounces uncooked, oven-ready lasagna noodles (8 noodles)

summary: The BEST Easy Healthy Lasagna requires approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes from start to finish. This recipe serves 6. One serving contains 467 calories, 44g of protein, and 16g of fat. If you have basil, salt, zucchini, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. This recipe from has 1 fans. Similar recipes include Easy Gift Lasagna, Easy Skillet Garden Lasagna, and Easy Vegan Lasagna.
instructions:
Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.

Cook the chopped onion and ground beef until the beef is fully cooked over medium-high heat in a large pan with high sides (about 10 minutes).

While the beef is cooking, cut the zucchini and summer squash into small, 1/4" - 1/2" cubes.

Once the beef is done cooking, set aside and drain.

Cook the zucchini and summer squash for about 7-10 minutes.

Add in the tomatoes, tomato sauce, and spices.

Continue cooking over medium heat for another 7-10 minutes, stirring often and breaking down the whole tomatoes with a spatula.

Add the cooked beef and onions back into the tomato sauce mixture and stir.

Pour about 1/4 of the tomato sauce mixture into a 9x13" casserole dish.

Place 4 of the lasagna noodles on top of the mixture, then add another 1/4 of the sauce on top of the noodles.

Add 1/2 of the cottage cheese to the casserole dish.

Top with 1/2 of the parmesan and 1/2 of the mozzarella.

Repeat steps 9-12 with the remaining ingredients.

Cover the casserole dish with foil and bake for 30 minutes.

Uncover and bake for another 15 minutes.

Let cool for a few minutes, then serve warm and enjoy!
